"title": "7317: blood, of Jesus Christ",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7317: blood, of jesus christ",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The shedding of the blood of Jesus Christ is seen as representing the giving of his life as an atoning sacrifice for the sins of humanity.</p>\n<h2>The blood of Jesus Christ as part of his humanity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:33-John19:34\">JHN 19:33–19:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:44\">LUK 22:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:28\">ACT 5:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:6\">1JN 5:6</a></p>\n<h2>The blood of Jesus Christ as a sacrifice</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:12-Heb9:14\">HEB 9:12–9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:23-Heb9:26\">HEB 9:23–9:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:3-Heb10:14\">HEB 10:3–10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:11-Heb13:12\">HEB 13:11–13:12</a></p>\n<h2>The blood of Jesus Christ as a symbol of atonement</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:25\">ROM 3:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7\">EPH 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:14\">REV 7:14</a></p>\n<h2>The effects of the blood of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>The institution of the new covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:25\">1CO 11:25</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:27-Matt26:28\">MAT 26:27–26:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:23-Mark14:24\">MRK 14:23–14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:20\">LUK 22:20</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:11-Heb9:15\">HEB 9:11–9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:24\">HEB 12:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:20\">HEB 13:20</a></p>\n<h3>Redemption</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:1-1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:1–1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18-1Pet1:19\">1PE 1:18–1:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9-Rev5:10\">REV 5:9–5:10</a></p>\n<h3>Forgiveness and justification</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:9\">ROM 5:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:28\">MAT 26:28</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:24\">MRK 14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:20\">LUK 22:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:25-Rom3:26\">ROM 3:25–3:26</a></p>\n<h3>Victory over evil and Satan</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:14-Rev7:17\">REV 7:14–7:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:10-Rev12:11\">REV 12:10–12:11</a></p>\n<h3>Liberation from sin</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:5-Rev1:6\">REV 1:5–1:6</a></p>\n<h3>The promise of total restoration</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:19-Col1:20\">COL 1:19–1:20</a></p>\n<h2>The blood of Jesus Christ and believers</h2>\n<h3>Believers are cleansed from all sin</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:14\">HEB 9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:22\">HEB 10:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:12\">HEB 13:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:6-1John1:9\">1JN 1:6–1:9</a></p>\n<h3>Believers have a new confidence before God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:13\">EPH 2:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:19-Col1:22\">COL 1:19–1:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:19-Heb10:22\">HEB 10:19–10:22</a></p>\n<h2>The blood of Jesus Christ and the Lord's Supper</h2>\n<h3>Invitations to share in the blood of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:16\">1CO 10:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:53-John6:57\">JHN 6:53–6:57</a></p>\n<h3>Warnings about sinning against the blood of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:27\">1CO 11:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:28-Heb10:31\">HEB 10:28–10:31</a></p>",
